The paper is about automatic speech recognition (ASR) in noisy environments, which is a common problem in speech processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and speech recognition. The paper also discusses speech enhancement measures, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound) or cs.SI (Signal Processing). The use of neural networks and machine learning techniques suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes a new baseline system for the CHiME-4 challenge, which could fall under cs.SD as it deals with speech processing in noisy environments.
